name: Manifest
comment: The Manifest class is used to maintain Manifest entry names and their associated Attributes. There are main Manifest Attributes as well as per-entry Attributes. For information on the Manifest format, please see the Manifest format specification.

constructors.name: Manifest
constructors.comment: Constructs a new Manifest from the specified input stream.

constructors.name: Manifest
constructors.comment: Constructs a new Manifest that is a copy of the specified Manifest.

methods.name: getMainAttributes
methods.comment: Returns the main Attributes for the Manifest.

methods.name: getEntries
methods.comment:
Returns a Map of the entries contained in this Manifest. Each entry
 is represented by a String name (key) and associated Attributes (value).
 The Map permits the {@code null} key, but no entry with a null key is
 created by {@link #read}, nor is such an entry written by using {@link
 #write}.

methods.name: getAttributes
methods.comment:
Returns the Attributes for the specified entry name. This method is defined as: 
      return (Attributes)getEntries().get(name)
Though {@code null} is a valid {@code name}, when {@code getAttributes(null)} is invoked on a {@code Manifest} obtained from a jar file, {@code null} will be returned. While jar files themselves do not allow {@code null}-named attributes, it is possible to invoke {@link #getEntries} on a {@code Manifest}, and on that result, invoke {@code put} with a null key and an arbitrary value. Subsequent invocations of {@code getAttributes(null)} will return the just-{@code put} value.

Note that this method does not return the manifest's main attributes; see {@link #getMainAttributes}.

methods.name: clear
methods.comment: Clears the main Attributes as well as the entries in this Manifest.

methods.name: write
methods.comment:
Writes the Manifest to the specified OutputStream.
 Attributes.Name.MANIFEST_VERSION must be set in
 MainAttributes prior to invoking this method.

methods.name: read
methods.comment:
Reads the Manifest from the specified InputStream. The entry
 names and attributes read will be merged in with the current
 manifest entries.

methods.name: equals
methods.comment:
Returns true if the specified Object is also a Manifest and has
 the same main Attributes and entries.

methods.name: hashCode
methods.comment: Returns the hash code for this Manifest.

methods.name: clone
methods.comment:
Returns a shallow copy of this Manifest. The shallow copy is implemented as follows: 
     public Object clone() { return new Manifest(this); }
